OL,4,Creduced after libel battle with Sunday
OL,5,CTimes
OL,7,FA hearing in June 2023 heard that
OL,8,FTimes Media's lawyers said its
OL,9,F"journalist's loss of phone was
OL,10,Finadvertent" and that Elphicke had
OL,11,F"chosen not to pursue issues relating
OL,12,Fto the defendant's disclosure before
OL,13,Fdiscontinuing his claim".
OL,15,FAccording to the judgment, the
OL,16,Fpublisher argued that Elphicke "had
OL,17,Flitigated his claim aggressively,
OL,18,Fmaking serious allegations against the
OL,19,Fdefendant and its journalists, its
OL,20,Fwitness and the complainant".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
